Tested with IPP 5.3 on Ubuntu 9.10 x86
--------------------------------------

Install ghc and cabal-install following the instructions at:

http://code.haskell.org/hmatrix/ghc.html

Add to .bahsrc

export IPP=/path/to/your/ipp/path/ia32/
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$IPP/sharedlib

$ wget http://perception.inf.um.es/~aruiz/CUDA.tar.gz

extract it to /path/to/CUDA and add to .bashrc

export CUDA=/path/to/CUDA

In a new terminal:

$ sudo apt-get install libgsl0-dev liblapack-dev
$ sudo apt-get install libghc6-glut-dev
$ sudo apt-get install nvidia-cg-toolkit libglew1.5-dev libdevil-dev g++
$ sudo apt-get install mplayer
$ sudo apt-get install darcs

$ cabal update
$ cd workdir
$ darcs get http://perception.inf.um.es/~aruiz/darcs/easyVision
$ cd easyVision/cabal
$ sh reinstall.sh

We can add to .bashrc the path to the working directory which contains cameras.def

export EASYVISION=/path/to/workdir/
